            <p>
                <small>
                    Dear Worker, thank you for your interest in our HITs! You are taking part in a large-scale research project conducted by the UKP Lab at the Technische Universit√§t Darmstadt, Germany.
                </small>
            </p>

            <h3>Task</h3>

            <p>
                There are {{numberOfArguments}} incomplete arguments to various topics written by a fictive person, John Doe.
            </p>
            <p>John comes from a far away (probably not the U.S.), so he has a different common sense knowledge and a rather peculiar way of reasoning.</p>
            <p>Your <strong>first task</strong> is the <strong>choose the most likely reason</strong> he used to make his argument.</p>
            <p>At the first moment, it might look that the reasons are contradictory to the argument and support its opposite. But some might be explained in a way that the argument eventually makes sense.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>However, in some cases neither reason really fits. Select the last option then.</li>
            </ul>

            <ul>
                <li>
                    Stay <strong>objective</strong> even if you strongly disagree with his views.
                </li>
            </ul>

            <p>If you chose one of the available reasons, your <strong>second task</strong> is to assess how hard was it and how logical the argument sounds.</p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    Remember that John does not share your world knowledge, so his explanations might sound silly yet still logical.
                </li>
            </ul>

            <p>Please ignore typos or small grammar errors.</p>

            <p>
                <small>By accepting this HIT, you agree that your submitted content will be licensed under Creative Commons CC0 (Public Domain) license.
                    <br/>
                    <strong>ATTENTION:</strong> The results will be processed by a state-of-the-art algorithm for detecting unreliable workers and checked manually for quality. Therefore it might take up to 7 days until the HITs are approved. Spammers will be revealed and rejected.
                </small>
            </p>

        </div>
        <div class="col-xs-12 col-md-6">


            <form name="mturk_form_name" id="mturk_form" method="post" action="{{mturkURL}}" data-type="claim">
                <!-- the value will be injected by mturk-required-script.js -->
                <input type="hidden" id="assignmentId" name="assignmentId" value=""/>

                {{#reasonClaimWarrantList}}
                    <div class="argument-box">
                        <div class="bg-success debate-title">
                            <h3>
                                <small>Debate question:</small>
                                {{title}}
                            </h3>
                            <p>
                                Additional info: {{description}}
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div id="{{reasonClaimWarrantId}}" class="argument">
                            <div class="sanity-check-box">John Doe argues:</div>
                            <div class="framed form-inline">
                                <div style="padding-top: 1em; padding-right: 1em">
                                    <p>
                                        <span id="{{reasonClaimWarrantId}}_selected_reason_text" class="selected-reason-text">Selected reason will be shown here.</span>
                                        And since
                                        <span id="{{reasonClaimWarrantId}}_warrant">{{alternativeWarrant}}</span>, I claim that {{stanceOpposingToAnnotatedStance}}
                                    </p>
                                </div>
                            </div>


                            <h4>Which reason fills the gap?</h4>

                            <div id="{{reasonClaimWarrantId}}_original_reason_group" class="stanceGroup">
                                {{#reasonOptions}}
                                    <div class="radio">
                                        <label id="{{reasonClaimWarrantId}}_reasonOption_{{value}}_label" style="margin-right: 10px">
                                            <input type="radio" name="{{reasonClaimWarrantId}}_original_reason_group" id="{{reasonClaimWarrantId}}_reasonOption_{{value}}" value="{{value}}" data-reasonid="{{reasonClaimWarrantId}}">
                                            {{reasonText}}
                                        </label>
                                    </div>
                                {{/reasonOptions}}
                            </div>

                            <div id="{{reasonClaimWarrantId}}_additionalQuestions" class="additional-questions" hidden>

                                <div class="sanity-check-box">Two additional questions</div>
                                <div class="framed">
                                    <p><strong>How hard was to infer the correct reason?</strong></p>
                                    <div id="{{reasonClaimWarrantId}}_familiarGroup" class="radio familiarGroup">
                                        <label style="margin-right: 10px">
                                            <input type="radio" name="{{reasonClaimWarrantId}}_familiarGroup" id="{{reasonClaimWarrantId}}_familiarGroup_0" value="0" data-reasonid="{{reasonClaimWarrantId}}">
                                            Pretty straightforward
                                        </label>
                                        <label style="margin-right: 10px">
                                            <input type="radio" name="{{reasonClaimWarrantId}}_familiarGroup" id="{{reasonClaimWarrantId}}_familiarGroup_1" value="1" data-reasonid="{{reasonClaimWarrantId}}">
                                            Required some thinking
                                        </label>
                                        <label style="margin-right: 10px">
                                            <input type="radio" name="{{reasonClaimWarrantId}}_familiarGroup" id="{{reasonClaimWarrantId}}_familiarGroup_2" value="2" data-reasonid="{{reasonClaimWarrantId}}">
                                            Quite tough
                                        </label>
                                    </div>

                                    <p><strong>How logical is the argument given the <span class="underlined-text">highlighted explanation</span>?</strong></p>
                                    <div id="{{reasonClaimWarrantId}}_logicalGroup" class="radio familiarGroup">
                                        <div class="checkbox">
                                            <label>
                                                <input type="radio" name="{{reasonClaimWarrantId}}_logicalGroup" id="{{reasonClaimWarrantId}}_logicalGroup_0" value="0" data-reasonid="{{reasonClaimWarrantId}}">
                                                Very weak logic, nobody would buy it
                                            </label>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="checkbox">
                                            <label>
                                                <input type="radio" name="{{reasonClaimWarrantId}}_logicalGroup" id="{{reasonClaimWarrantId}}_logicalGroup_1" value="1" data-reasonid="{{reasonClaimWarrantId}}">
                                                Sounds logical but has some flaws
                                            </label>
                                        </div>
                                        <div class="checkbox">
                                            <label>
                                                <input type="radio" name="{{reasonClaimWarrantId}}_logicalGroup" id="{{reasonClaimWarrantId}}_logicalGroup_2" value="2" data-reasonid="{{reasonClaimWarrantId}}">
                                                The logic makes sense and I can imagine people would buy the argument
                                            </label>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>

